<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="593" pageId="3" pageNumber="591" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1405,1957]" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1604,1629]" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[321,564,1604,1629]" pageId="3" pageNumber="591" refId="ref2701" refString="Kishii, T. &amp; Jiang, S. - H. (1999) Notes on the Chinese Elateridae (Coleoptera) (4). The entomological review of Japan, 54 (1), 11 - 19." type="journal article">Kishii &amp; Jiang (1999)</bibRefCitation>
first recorded this species in Northeast 
<collectingRegion box="[1003,1177,1604,1629]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">
Inner 
<collectingCountry box="[1068,1177,1604,1629]" name="Mongolia" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
(Ganhe Town [甘河镇], in Hulun Buir City [呼伦贝尔市]) and North 
<collectingRegion box="[689,787,1644,1669]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
(Habahe County [哈巴河县] and Fuyun County [富蕴县]) and treated the recorded specimens as subspecies 
<taxonomicName box="[748,955,1680,1704]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Pristilophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="melancholicus" subSpecies="tianshanicus">
<emphasis box="[748,955,1680,1704]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">S. m. tianshanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; however, 
<bibRefCitation box="[1083,1347,1680,1705]" pageId="3" pageNumber="591" refId="ref2821" refString="Schimmel, R., Tarnawski, D., Han, T. &amp; Platia, G. (2015) Polish entomological monographs. Vol. 11. Monograph of the new tribe Selatosomini from China (Elateridae: Denticollinae). Part 1: genera Pristilophus Latreille, 1834 stat. nov., Selatosomus Stephens, 1830, Warchalowskia (Tarnawski, 1995) stat. nov., and Sinophotistus gen. nov. Polish Entomological Society, Poznan, 328 pp." type="book">
Schimmel 
<emphasis box="[1205,1264,1680,1704]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">et al.</emphasis>
(2015)
</bibRefCitation>
did not include the record. In this article, the specimens examined from 
<collectingRegion box="[921,1019,1716,1741]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1083,1263,1716,1741]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">
Inner 
<collectingCountry box="[1154,1263,1716,1741]" name="Mongolia" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
confirmed the occurrence of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[491,561,1752,1777]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">China</collectingCountry>
. The specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[820,918,1752,1777]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
have a dark green metallic reflection on the elytra (
<figureCitation box="[231,331,1788,1813]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1659,1681]" captionTargetBox="[176,1343,205,1614]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[171,1407,193,1631]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–F. Pristilophus melancholicus. A–C.male from Xinjiang:A.dorsal view; B. ventral view; C. aedeagus, ventral view. D–F. male from Inner mongolia: D. dorsal view; E. ventral view; F. aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars 2 mm for A–B, D–E; 0.5 mm for C and F." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1245452/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">Fig. 3 A</figureCitation>
), the pronotum and abdomen are blackish brown (
<figureCitation box="[906,1038,1788,1813]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1659,1681]" captionTargetBox="[176,1343,205,1614]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[171,1407,193,1631]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–F. Pristilophus melancholicus. A–C.male from Xinjiang:A.dorsal view; B. ventral view; C. aedeagus, ventral view. D–F. male from Inner mongolia: D. dorsal view; E. ventral view; F. aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars 2 mm for A–B, D–E; 0.5 mm for C and F." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1245452/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">Fig. 3 A–B</figureCitation>
), apex of the paramere has a small hook (
<figureCitation box="[224,321,1824,1849]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1659,1681]" captionTargetBox="[176,1343,205,1614]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[171,1407,193,1631]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–F. Pristilophus melancholicus. A–C.male from Xinjiang:A.dorsal view; B. ventral view; C. aedeagus, ventral view. D–F. male from Inner mongolia: D. dorsal view; E. ventral view; F. aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars 2 mm for A–B, D–E; 0.5 mm for C and F." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1245452/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">Fig. 3 C</figureCitation>
), the male (
<quantity box="[457,561,1825,1849]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0699999999999998" pageId="3" pageNumber="591" unit="mm" value="10.7">10.7 mm</quantity>
) is much smaller than the female (
<quantity box="[959,1065,1825,1849]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.41" pageId="3" pageNumber="591" unit="mm" value="14.1">14.1 mm</quantity>
); while the specimen from 
<collectingRegion country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">
Inner 
<collectingCountry box="[151,260,1860,1885]" name="Mongolia" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
show some differences from the former, which has a green metallic reflection on the elytra and purple metallic reflection at the base of elytra (
<figureCitation box="[603,701,1896,1921]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1659,1681]" captionTargetBox="[176,1343,205,1614]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[171,1407,193,1631]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–F. Pristilophus melancholicus. A–C.male from Xinjiang:A.dorsal view; B. ventral view; C. aedeagus, ventral view. D–F. male from Inner mongolia: D. dorsal view; E. ventral view; F. aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars 2 mm for A–B, D–E; 0.5 mm for C and F." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1245452/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">Fig. 3 D</figureCitation>
), the pronotum and abdomen are black (
<figureCitation box="[1159,1289,1896,1921]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1659,1681]" captionTargetBox="[176,1343,205,1614]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[171,1407,193,1631]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–F. Pristilophus melancholicus. A–C.male from Xinjiang:A.dorsal view; B. ventral view; C. aedeagus, ventral view. D–F. male from Inner mongolia: D. dorsal view; E. ventral view; F. aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars 2 mm for A–B, D–E; 0.5 mm for C and F." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1245452/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">Fig. 3 D–E</figureCitation>
), apex of the paramere has a large hook (
<figureCitation box="[460,551,1932,1957]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1659,1681]" captionTargetBox="[176,1343,205,1614]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[171,1407,193,1631]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–F. Pristilophus melancholicus. A–C.male from Xinjiang:A.dorsal view; B. ventral view; C. aedeagus, ventral view. D–F. male from Inner mongolia: D. dorsal view; E. ventral view; F. aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars 2 mm for A–B, D–E; 0.5 mm for C and F." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1245452/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="591">Fig. 3 F</figureCitation>
), the male specimen is about 
<quantity box="[882,985,1932,1957]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.46" pageId="3" pageNumber="591" unit="mm" value="14.6">14.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1245452/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="592" startId="4.[151,250,1659,1681]" targetBox="[176,1343,205,1614]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1435,1659,1743]" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1659,1681]" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
A–F. 
<taxonomicName box="[337,613,1659,1681]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Pristilophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melancholicus">
<emphasis box="[337,613,1659,1681]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">Pristilophus melancholicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A–C. male from Xinjiang: A. dorsal view; B. ventral view; C. aedeagus, ventral view. D–F. male from Inner mongolia: D. dorsal view; E. ventral view; F. aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars 2 mm for A–B, D–E; 0.5 mm for C and F.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1782,2023]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="593" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">
This species is widely distributed from Europe to the Russian Far East (
<collectingRegion box="[1018,1153,1782,1807]" country="Russia" name="Kamchatka" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">Kamchatka</collectingRegion>
). Historically, there were many subspecies and variations, but only three subspecies are currently recognized (
<bibRefCitation box="[1118,1304,1818,1843]" pageId="4" pageNumber="592" refId="ref2995" refString="Tarnawski, D. (1995) A Revision of the Genus Selatosomus Stephens, 1830 (Coleoptera: Elateridae: Athoinae: Ctenicerini). BS [Biologica Silesiae], Wroclaw, 183 pp." type="book">Tarnawski 1995</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation pageId="4" pageNumber="592" refId="ref2617" refString="Cate, P. C., Sanchez-Ruiz, A., Lobl, I. &amp; Smetana, A. (2007) Elateridae. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Smetana, A. (Ed.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 4. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 89 - 209." type="book">
Cate 
<emphasis box="[1378,1436,1818,1842]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
). According to the previous studies (
<bibRefCitation box="[651,841,1854,1879]" pageId="4" pageNumber="592" refId="ref2995" refString="Tarnawski, D. (1995) A Revision of the Genus Selatosomus Stephens, 1830 (Coleoptera: Elateridae: Athoinae: Ctenicerini). BS [Biologica Silesiae], Wroclaw, 183 pp." type="book">Tarnawski 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[857,1102,1854,1879]" pageId="4" pageNumber="592" refId="ref2701" refString="Kishii, T. &amp; Jiang, S. - H. (1999) Notes on the Chinese Elateridae (Coleoptera) (4). The entomological review of Japan, 54 (1), 11 - 19." type="journal article">Kishii &amp; Jiang 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[1119,1377,1854,1879]" pageId="4" pageNumber="592" refId="ref2821" refString="Schimmel, R., Tarnawski, D., Han, T. &amp; Platia, G. (2015) Polish entomological monographs. Vol. 11. Monograph of the new tribe Selatosomini from China (Elateridae: Denticollinae). Part 1: genera Pristilophus Latreille, 1834 stat. nov., Selatosomus Stephens, 1830, Warchalowskia (Tarnawski, 1995) stat. nov., and Sinophotistus gen. nov. Polish Entomological Society, Poznan, 328 pp." type="book">
Schimmel 
<emphasis box="[1244,1306,1854,1878]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
), the population from 
<collectingRegion box="[343,441,1890,1915]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName box="[577,1035,1890,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Pristilophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="melancholicus" subSpecies="tianshanicus">
<emphasis box="[577,1035,1890,1914]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">Pristilophus melancholicus tianshanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; while the subspecies status of the population from 
<collectingRegion box="[346,643,1926,1951]" inferredBySuffix="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">
Northeast 
<collectingRegion box="[465,643,1926,1951]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">
Inner 
<collectingCountry box="[534,643,1926,1951]" name="Mongolia" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
</collectingRegion>
needs to be further confirmed, noting that the gap between the two localities measures more than 
<quantity box="[489,594,1962,1987]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="592" unit="km" value="2400.0">2,400 km</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[609,703,1962,1987]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,912,934]" captionTargetBox="[189,1394,339,891]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1394,339,891]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–B. Distribution maps: A. Selatosomus huanghaoi Qiu, new species in Yunnan; B. recorded localities of Pristilophus melancholicus in China." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1245454/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">Fig. 4 B</figureCitation>
). Moreover, the only two specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[1177,1352,1962,1987]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">
Inner 
<collectingCountry box="[1243,1352,1962,1987]" name="Mongolia" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation pageId="4" pageNumber="592" refId="ref2701" refString="Kishii, T. &amp; Jiang, S. - H. (1999) Notes on the Chinese Elateridae (Coleoptera) (4). The entomological review of Japan, 54 (1), 11 - 19." type="journal article">Kishii &amp; Jiang 1999 and this study</bibRefCitation>
) show distinct difference in the hook of paramere (comparing with 
<figureCitation box="[1231,1401,1998,2023]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1659,1681]" captionTargetBox="[176,1343,205,1614]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[171,1407,193,1631]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–F. Pristilophus melancholicus. A–C.male from Xinjiang:A.dorsal view; B. ventral view; C. aedeagus, ventral view. D–F. male from Inner mongolia: D. dorsal view; E. ventral view; F. aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars 2 mm for A–B, D–E; 0.5 mm for C and F." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1245452/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">Figs. 3b and 3c</figureCitation>
shown in 
<bibRefCitation box="[260,508,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="593" refId="ref2701" refString="Kishii, T. &amp; Jiang, S. - H. (1999) Notes on the Chinese Elateridae (Coleoptera) (4). The entomological review of Japan, 54 (1), 11 - 19." type="journal article">Kishii &amp; Jiang (1999)</bibRefCitation>
, the new material studied in this article has bigger hook in parameres). Since it’s a very widely distributed species, and because of the inadequate samples, it’s still difficult to verify the subspecies and clarify the variations of different populations.
</paragraph>
